  "text": "Mascot 2.2 (Matrix Science) was used for protein identification by searching the Swissprot database of Mus musculus [CITATION_1] . Mass tolerance for intact peptide masses was 20 ppm for MALDI MS data and 10 ppm for Orbitrap data, respectively. Mass tolerance for fragment ions detected in the linear ion trap was 0.8 Da. Oxidation of methionine and phosphorylation of serine, threonine, and tyrosine were set as variable modifications.",
